This project uses SQL and SQL Lite to analyze business data and answer business operational questions. By querying a relational database, 
the project uncovers insights related to customer behavior, revenue trends, employee compensation, and customer loyalty. 

This goal is to demonstrate SQL profiency within real-world scenarios. 


bais_sqlite_lab.db → Source database
challenge.sql → Contains all SQL queries used to answer the business questions
INSIGHTS.md → Written analysis and key findings from the queries

Business Questions Solved

1. Top 5 Customers by Total Spend

Identifies the highest-value customers based on total purchase amount.

2. Total Revenue by Product Category

Analyzes which product categories generate the most revenue.

3. Employees Earning Above Department Average

Finds employees whose salaries exceed their department’s average, highlighting compensation differences.

4. Cities with the Most Loyal Customers

Determines which cities have the highest number of “Gold” loyalty customers.

What I Learned
How to write complex SQL queries using joins across multiple tables
How to aggregate and analyze data using GROUP BY and HAVING
How to translate raw query results into meaningful business insights
The importance of data-driven decision making in real-world scenarios

How to run project:

Open the project in VS Code (or any SQLite-compatible tool)
Install the SQLTools extension with the SQLite driver
Load the bais_sqlite_lab.db database
Open and execute queries from challenge.sql
Review outputs and compare with insights in INSIGHTS.md

